                                    <p class="making_bold">Disputes (Resolutions) Policy</p>
                                    <p>Generally, transactions are conducted smoothly on Gharobaar. However there may be some cases where both the Buyers and Sellers may face issues. At Gharobaar, we have a Dispute Resolution process in order to resolve disputes between Buyers and Sellers.</p>
                                    <p class="making_bold">What is a 'dispute'?</p>
                                    <p>A 'Dispute' can be defined as a disagreement between a Buyer/Service Recipient and a Seller/Service Provider in connection with a transaction on the Platform.</p>
                                    <p class="making_bold">How does a 'dispute' occur in the Marketplace?</p>
                                    <p>Disputes are filed as a result of a disagreement between the Buyer/Service Recipient and the Seller/Service Provider. Disputes arise out of an issue that is raised by either party not being completely satisfied with the resolution of their complaint/issue.</p>
                                    <p>It is important that before a Buyer/Service Recipient or Seller/Service Provider raises a dispute, they should attempt to solve the issue. Please note that whenever a Buyer/Service Recipient raises a dispute, the Seller/Service Provider's payment for that order is put on hold immediately until the issue is resolved.</p>
                                    <p class="making_bold">How is a 'dispute' created?</p>
                                    <p>Whenever there is a disagreement, the Buyer/Service Recipient can write to letstalk@gharobaar.com, while the Seller/Service Provider can write to sellerhelp@gharobaar.com, in order to raise a dispute. Disputes can be raised at a particular transaction level.</p>
                                    <p class="making_bold">What are the various types of 'disputes'?</p>
                                    <p>Following are the indicative examples of potential disputes:</p><br>
                                    <p>For Food Products:</p>
                                    <p>Issue related to quality of product</p>
                                    <p>Issue related to packaging </p>
                                    <p>Issue related to quantity of product</p>
                                    <p>Others</p>
                                    <p>For Non Food Products:</p>
                                    <p>Display image different from product delivered</p>
                                    <p>Product description varies from actual</p>
                                    <p>Size or Dimensions of the Product</p>
                                    <p>Colour </p>
                                    <p>Damaged/Defective Product Received</p>
                                    <p>Others</p>
                                    <p>For Services:</p>
                                    <p>Service provided did not show up.</p>
                                    <p>Service provider did not comply with Appointment time. </p>
                                    <p>Service provider had some infrastructural issue</p>
                                    <p>Unprofessional Behaviour of service provider.</p>
                                    <p style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:500;font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;">Others</p>
